@node Introduction "BJScan - Introduction"

@{b}Introduction and Features
#########################@{ub}

BJscan is a reverse catalog viewer designed and written for DayDream BBS.
It's written because the standard reverse viewer, that comes with the just
mentioned BBS package, is way too limited.
A couple of features of BJScan:

- It is a DDDP door.

- Full support with 18 characters long filenames catalogs!
  - you can disable the NUMBERS in the configuration by changing the
    the value behind NUMBERS18 to N. BJScan will now print the dates
    instead of filenumbers.

- NUMBERS supports up to 9999 entries in one catalog!

- entries are marked by either using the FLAG command or by using the
  marker (cursor keys and <-')

- Hotkeys!

- very @{" configurable " Link Configure}

- Displays 'BJScanning...' instead of 'Running Ext. Door' when a user uses
  the internal DayDream WHO command when another user is using BJScan

- controlled through menubars
  - viewer menu
    - MORE        scroll one page back in time
    - PAGE DOWN   clear screen and go one page back in time
    - DIZ DOWN    go back one entry in time
    - DIZ UP      clear screen and advance one entry in time
    - GOTO        enter the GOTO menu
    - SEARCH      search a string in the current catalog
                  @{b}(hotkey: Z)@{ub}
    - FLAG        flag entries by filenames or filenumbers
                  - Supports #? and * wildcards when flagging filenames!
                    You can also flag multiple filenames, example:
                    'RYLDD120.LHA RYLDD120.NFO' will flag both specified
                    entries.
                  - Ability to flag multiple entries by number, example:
                    '100 101 102' will flag entries 100, 101 and 102 but
                    you can also use '100-102'!!
                  @{b}(Hotkey: F)@{ub}
    - QUIT        quit BJScan
                  @{b}(Hoteky: ESC, Q)@{ub}
  - marker menu (entered by using the cursor-up key)
    - MARK        mark/unmark highlighted entry for download
    - VIEW        view highlighted entry using internal DayDream view-cmd
    - TAG         tag/untag highlighted entry for FAKER or MOVE
    - BACK        return to the VIEWER menu
    - FAKER       execute FAKER to fake @{u}tagged@{uu} entries (restricted access)
    - MOVE        move tagged entries (restricted access)
    - WHO D/L'ED  retrieve download information from the highlighted entry
  - goto menu
    - GOTO DAY    use cursor keys to pick day, <-' to make it so
    - GOTO NUMBER enter filenumber you wish to go to
    - HOME        go to the beginning of the reversed catalog
    - END         go to the end of the reversed catalog
    - CATALOG     reverse an other catalog within the current conference
    - HELP        display DayDream:Configs/BJScan.HELP
    - INFO        view some information and statistics about BJScan
    - BACK        return to the VIEWER menu

- displays percentage and local time at the far left side in the menubars!

- inbuild FAKER with more features than the standard faker that comes
  with the DayDream package.
  - ability to tag multiple files, in order to fake multiple files at once
    with the same settings!!!!
  - COMMENTs can be 79 characters wide!!
    - COMMENT-presets are configurable (DayDream:Configs/BJScan/BJScan.FAKER'
    - COMMENTs are changed by either pressing <-' while COMMENT is
      highlighted in the fakermenu or by pressing the cursor-up key at any
      desired moment in the fakermenu.
    - ability to switch it ON or OFF (green (=on) or red (=off) gadget)
    - ability to center the COMMENT by using ALT-C
      @{b}(Hotkey: ALT-C)@{ub}
    - ability to walk through the predefined comments  using the TAB key!
      (standard comments are retrieved from 'DayDream:Configs/BJSCAN.FAKER')
      @{b}(Hotkey: TAB)@{ub}
  - ability to make the tagged entry/entries FREE to download
  - ability to DELETE tagged entry/entries
  - NUKE to punnish or reward the user who U/L'ed the tagged entry
  - RETURN CREDITS to all user who leeched the, to be faked, entries
  - seperate menu to alter color and style of the comment-text (entered by
    pressing the up-arrow key while user is editing the COMMENT)
    - Foreground colors can be any of the 8 colors that DayDream BBS offers.
      @{b}(Hotkeys: 0, 1...8@{ub})
    - Background colors can be any of the 8 colors that DayDream BBS offers.
      @{b}(Hotkeys: SHIFT-0, SHIFT-1....SHIFT-8)@{ub}
    - supports Bold, Italic and Underline styled comments!
      @{b}(Hotkeys: B, I and U)@{ub}
    - return to FAKER menu by pressing the cursor-down key

- written in assembler language !!

- Full support for ASCII terminals

- A nice right-to-left scrolltext appears after IDLE time period!

- You can get a personal registered version of BJScan!

- You can download the latest BJScan from
  - WILD PALMS  +31.(0)30.6037959, SysOp: Radavi/Effect^Royal
  - ENGINEERING +31.(0)546.821ask, SysOp: Paris/Project A Inc.

- And a lot more... !!!

@endnode
@node Requirements "BJScan - Requirements and Installation"

@{b}Requirements
############@{ub}

- DayDream BBS V1.17+ by Antti Häyrynen aka Hydra/iNSANE

- Amiga Operating System 3.X

- BJScan.CFG <provided within this package>

- BJScan.DATELINE <provided within this package>



@{b}Installation
############@{ub}

To install, copy the 'Doors:BJScan' from this package to your 'Doors:'-
directory.
Create a new directory in your 'DayDream:Configs/' called 'BJScan' and
copy the files located in the directory with same name from this package
into it.

Add the following lines to your 'External Commands'-settings in your
'DayDream:DayDream.CFG':

------------------------------------------------kut-----
;External Commands
DOOR_COMMAND.. FR
DOOR_TYPE..... 1
DOOR_SECURITY. 5
DOOR_EXECUTE.. Doors:BJScan %N
+
<other_commands>
------------------------------------------------kut-----


@endnode
@node Configuration "BJScan - Configuration"

@{b}Configuration
#############@{ub}

  @{b}DayDream:Configs/BJScan/BJScan.CFG@{ub}

   NUMBERS........ Y
   This will activate/deactivate the numbers infront of each entry.

   NUMBERS18...... Y
   This enables the numbers infront of ech entry in an LONGNAMES directory.
   Note that the date disappears when you've turned NUMBERS18 on.

   COLORNUMBER.... <Esc>[0;31m (ansi codes)

   COLORNAME...... <Esc>[0;37m (ansi codes)

   COLORCURRPOS... <Esc>[0;30;47m (ansi codes)

   COLORFLAGS..... <Esc>[34m (ansi codes)

   COLORSIZE...... <Esc>[33m (ansi codes)

   COLORDATE...... <Esc>[35m (ansi codes)

   COLORDESC...... <Esc>[37m (ansi codes)

   COLORNEWFILE... <Esc>[0;32m (ansi codes)
   The color of the NEWFILECHAR.

   NEWFILECHAR.... * (1 character)
   The character that is placed behind every entry that is new to the online
   user.

   COLORMARKED.... <esc>[0;31m
   The color of the MARKEDCHAR

   MARKEDCHAR..... *
   The character that is placed behind every entry that the online user has
   marked.

   COLORTAGGED.... <esc>[0;32m
   The color of the TAGGEDCHAR.

   TAGGEDCHAR..... $
   The character that is placed behind every entry that the online user has
   tagged (faker).

   AUTODOWN....... Y
   When Y, the highlight-bar will move an entry down when the online user
   uses MARK or TAG.

   SEPARATOR...... <string>
   When specified, this line is placed between every two entries.
   Note that the program slows down when you've specified this option.


  @{b}DayDream:Configs/BJScan/BJScan.Dateline@{ub}

   The file BJSCAN.DATALINE contains the display which will be shown everytime
   the date changes in the file-catalog. Week number, day name & number, month
   name and year number are supported.
   Current version only supports full names & numbers instead of number (i.e.
   September, instead of 09). You can use the following options:

   %w  = week number (will print a 2 character string, like 01, 12, 48 etc.)

   %d? = day (like: 'Today, 13 september 1995')
         at the ? you can use: c = centered
                               l = left alligned
                               r = right alligned
         to alter the color, you can use 6 <Esc> sequences to alter the colors
         of the printed text, like:
         %dc<Esc>[0;45;37m<Esc>[37m<Esc>[34m<Esc>[37m<Esc>[34m<Esc>[37m

   %D  = day (like: 06-10-95)
         to alter the color, you can use 5 <Esc> sequences to alter the colors
         of the digits, like: <Esc>[37m<Esc>[34m<Esc>[37m<Esc>[34m<Esc>[37m


  @{b}DayDream:Configs/BJScan/BJScan.Faker@{ub}

   This file contains some default templates, which can be picked in the FAKER
   COMMENT option, by pressing TAB.
   You can add/remove entries the same way you edit the other configuration
   files of BJScan.
   Note that the maximum length of an entry is 79 characters!!


  @{b}DayDream:Configs/BJScan/BJScan.Help@{ub}

   This file should contain a plain ASCII/ANSI color/control codes screen which
   should contain some usefull information for the online user.
   The standard help sucks and is not up-to-date. Make your own, we didn't had
   the time nor spirit to make you one.. :(

@endnode
@node History "BJScan - Revision History"

@{b}Revision History
################@{ub}

1.0   MAJOR DISASTER! BAD CODE! What was I thinkin'?

1.1   COMPLETE REWRITE, YEAH, LOOKS PROMISING!!!

1.2   Fixed  : When the list arrived at 100%, things fucked up!!
      Added  : When list arrives at 100%, you have the choice to
               to continue to next filelist!!!
      Added  : Fixed width of date in DateLine (xx-xx-xx)

1.3   Added  : AUTODOWN
      Added  : Search/Continue Search
      Added  : GOTO/-DAY

1.3r2 Some minor changes by Paris / Project A Inc.
        Fixed  : MENUCHAR (was still hardcoded)
        Fixed  : NEWFILECHAR (was still hardcoded)
        Changed: fixed strings a bit

1.4r1 Added  : NUMBERS in front of filenames can be turned on/off

1.4r2 Added  : Multiple fileflagging and numberflagging, finally!

1.5r1 Changed: Rewrote large pieces of source. Source looks much better now!
      Fixed  : Catalogs are picked more wisely now.
      Changed: Redesigned the menubar system.
      Fixed  : PromptUser
      Added  : Current Time/Percentage is shown left of menubar

1.5r2 Due to a bug in DayDream 1.17, FetchKey() is avoided!!

1.6r1 FetchKey() refitted
      Added  : Possiblity to detag tagged files
      Added  : GOTO DAY => Removed: GOTO/DAY BACK
      Fixed  : A bug in HOME
      Changed: the look of the menu bar a bit

1.6r2 Fixed  : Percentage
      Added  : GOTO END
      Added  : GOTO NUMBER (hotkey = ':' )

1.6r3 Added  : 18 characters long filenames support (finally!)
      Added  : NUMBERS18, Yes will not display current date
      Fixed  : Bug in GOTO DAY
      Fixed  : Bug in SEARCH
      Changed: SEARCH hotkey to 'Z'
      Changed: Tag-routines

1.6r4 Added  : FAKER <finally!>

1.6r5 Added  : MOVE command to MarkMenu (inoperatve at this time)
      Changed: FAKE -> TAG (bcoz of MOVE command)
      Added  : hotkey 'F' in mark menu to reset all fake flags
      Added  : FAKER / MOVE are only reachable by users with a
               securitylevel of >=250 (not yet configurable)
      Added  : CATALOG in Goto-menu to change catalogs

1.6r6 Changed: path to the BJScan config-files to 'DayDream:Configs/BJScan/'
      Added  : Made the faker-presets configurable
      Fixed  : bug in FAKER-COMMENT


